    "enonce": {
      "texte": "\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELesson 26: Compound Adjectives\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cbr\u003ERead the rules and choose the correct option to complete each sentence.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERule reminder:\u003C/strong\u003E Compound adjectives are formed by joining two words (often with a hyphen) to describe a noun. Common patterns: \u003Cem\u003Eadjective \u002B noun (well-known), number \u002B noun (five-minute), noun \u002B adjective (world-famous), noun \u002B past participle (sun-kissed), adjective \u002B past participle (easy-going)\u003C/em\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E",
      "images": []
    },
